Title: Data or State Flow Diagram
Describe: State moves through JSON files, global dictionaries, message lists, queues, and thread-owned local context.
------------------------------------------------------------
[Example]
S07_DATA_OR_STATE_FLOW: Task lifecycle

[Description]
Tasks start in `pending` through `create_task`, which writes `.tasks/task_*.json`.

`claim_task` requires a pending task with no owner and successful dependency checks through `can_start`, then changes status to `in_progress`.

`complete_task` accepts only `in_progress`, changes status to `completed`, and reports newly unblocked pending tasks.

`bind_task_to_worktree` can attach a worktree name to a task record.

[UML]
None

[Detail]
The lifecycle explanation shows valid transitions and rejection paths.

The state is persisted in `.tasks` JSON files rather than a transactional database.

`can_start` returns false when a dependency id is missing or incomplete.

`claim_task` includes missing and incomplete dependencies in its return message.

If maintainers add task states, they must update `claim_task`, `complete_task`, `scan_unclaimed_tasks`, and display functions such as `run_list_tasks`.

------------------------------------------------------------
[Example]
Message and context dataflow

[Description]
User input, teammate messages, protocol replies, cron events, and background task results all eventually enter `messages` or `history`.

`prepare_context` shrinks large tool results, trims old message ranges, micro-compacts earlier tool results, and calls `compact_history` when `estimate_size(messages)` exceeds `CONTEXT_LIMIT`.

Background results first land in `background_results`, then later become XML-like notifications.

[UML]
@startuml
left to right direction
component "User input" as UserInput
component "cron_queue" as CronQueue
component "background_results" as BackgroundResults
component ".mailboxes/*.jsonl" as Mailbox
component "messages/history" as Messages
component "prepare_context" as Prepare
database ".transcripts\n.task_outputs/tool-results" as Persisted
component "Anthropic request" as Request
UserInput -- Messages
CronQueue -- Messages : scheduled prompt
BackgroundResults -- Messages : task_notification
Mailbox -- Messages : inbox and protocol content
Messages -- Prepare
Prepare -- Persisted : transcript or large output
Prepare -- Request : trimmed or compacted messages
@enduml

[Detail]
Arrows show data movement.

`messages` is the central model-context cache; files and queues are different entry points into it.

`tool_result_budget` can persist large output under `.task_outputs/tool-results` and return only a path plus preview to the model.

That controls context growth, but follow-up work must be able to reread persisted output when the preview is insufficient.
